<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Light2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Light,</orth> adj. bright, clear: <cit><quote>that, thou being dead, the day should yet be l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1134" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1134</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>dark is l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.269" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 269</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>before the sun rose he was harnessed l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>earth-treading stars that make dark heaven l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>more l. and l. it grows,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>made the night l. with drinking,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 182</bibl></cit>. Play on the word: <bibl n="shak. luc 1434" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1434</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.280" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 280</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 6, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 151</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>